text: Rosalie is a 1937 American musical movie. It was directed by W.S. Van Dyke. The movie stars Eleanor Powell, Nelson Eddy and Frank Morgan. It is an adaptation of the 1928 stage musical of the same name, The movue was released in December 1937. It follows the story of the musical but replaces most of the Broadway score with new songs by Cole Porter. The story is about the romantic entanglements of a princess in disguise and a West Point cadet. Category:American musical movies Category:1937 movies
title: Rosalie
